VERDICT: GREEN — the discrimination claim REPRODUCES and, at the near-duplicate regime (cos>=0.995,
sigma<=0.02), EXCEEDS the paper: v2 = 37.6x @ cos~1.0 and 8.4x @ cos 0.9998, vs the paper's ~17x @
cos>=0.995 and vs the in-tree v1's 1.2x. Discrimination degrades gracefully with noise (correct: more
noise = less similar = should dedup less). Frontier plateau is rich (76 vs v1's 2). Dominance check is
fast (16.66 ns/pair).

HONEST SCOPE:
 - plateau 76 != the paper's ~307 (different encoder params: SP_KMD_ANCHORS=14/RESID=60/LMAX=8, K=128).
   Qualitatively rich, not degenerate; the exact 307 belongs to the old-repo config, not re-tuned here.
 - encode cost 9.13 us/vec is qsort(128)-bound; the hot-path dominance check is 16.66 ns. If ever wired
   into a live KV path, replace the full sort with a partial top-(A+R) selection.
 - this is a CPU-core encoder + signature; it is NOT yet wired into the served daemon or the PoUW sieve
   (which still uses frozen v1). Wiring is a separate task if the sieve is ever reprioritized.
